357
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,040
Oh, the handsome bro.

358
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:20,480
Remember me?

359
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:23,000
- Remember?
- Hey!

360
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:23,640
Remember?

361
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:26,080
- “Treasure of the island.”
- That’s right.

362
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:28,960
I sold you on the treasure of the island.

363
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,320
Well, well, well.

364
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,080
Looks like my effort paid off after all.

365
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:35,000
You guys were all over each other.

366
00:33:35,600 --> 00:33:37,200
And here I thought
you weren’t interested.

367
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:41,000
So, what do you think?

368
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:43,720
My bro’s really something, huh?

369
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:52,240
I’m pretty skilled,
if I do say so myself.

370
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:53,480
Don’t you think so?

371
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,160
I’m going to let everyone know

372
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:04,200
that you and your lackey
are in cahoots to trick tourists.

373
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:08,199
About the treasure of the island stuff?

374
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:10,800
I didn’t force you to buy me.

375
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:16,320
I’d better tell you something.

376
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,719
- I don’t want to know.
- But I want to tell you.

377
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,120
- I don’t want to listen.
- Just listen for a bit.

378
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:20,600
No.

379
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,960
Then I’ll just talk to myself.

380
00:34:23,840 --> 00:34:24,560
I admit.

381
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:28,560
I paid Ai Palm to advertise
to the resort’s guests.

382
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:30,960
See? I knew it.

383
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:35,360
I’m going to tell the resort manager that
you and your bro are deceiving the guests.

384
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:39,480
But I paid him to advertise
my diving packages.

385
00:34:39,639 --> 00:34:40,560
But I heard it.

386
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:41,760
Look.

387
00:34:42,679 --> 00:34:44,159
Why would I sell my body?

388
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:45,920
I'm not a prostitute.

389
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:47,840
He's the one saying all that.

390
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:55,080
Do you really think a small
operator’s diving packages

391
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:57,280
will be included in a resort's services?

392
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:02,200
It’s not that simple.

393
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:04,160
At first

394
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,960
I hired the local kids

395
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,680
and asked my friends working at resorts

396
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,560
to promote them to the guests.

397
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,720
I’d been doing that for years.

398
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:17,120
Even got kicked out sometimes.

399
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:19,360
It wasn’t until recently

400
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:23,200
that people started showing
interest in local businesses.

401
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,000
Some resorts are willing
to support the locals.

402
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:29,800
The resort you’re staying in
is one of them.

403
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:32,480
Hey.

404
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:37,640
Why don’t you tell him that
you’re the leader of the locals too?

405
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:39,800
He may not look it

406
00:35:40,120 --> 00:35:43,000
but he’s the force behind
the people around here.

407
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:46,040
People used to laugh at him.

408
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:47,280
And look at him now.

409
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:48,680
So fluent in foreign languages.

410
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:52,560
Even the resort higher-ups are
willing to have a chat with him.

411
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:56,840
And this place got
some help from him too.

412
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:58,880
When did I ever help you?

413
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,560
It was all your doing.
It’s got nothing to do with me.

414
00:36:01,640 --> 00:36:04,360
Little brat, you blew off my compliment.

415
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:07,760
You’re always like this, you brat.

416
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:08,840
I’m so pissed.

417
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:17,720
What’s wrong?

418
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:21,480
Are you looking at me like that
because you've fallen for me?

419
00:36:36,880 --> 00:36:37,680
Those boats.

420
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:39,280
Are they all fishing boats?

421
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,000
That’s right.

422
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,400
There used to be more of them.

423
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:50,600
The one you’re looking at
belongs to my dad.

424
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:52,360
Your boat?

425
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:54,560
My dad’s, not mine.

426
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:56,840
Same difference.

427
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,080
No.

428
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:00,480
It's not the same thing

429
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:03,120
because my dad cut ties
with me a long time ago.

430
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:08,560
My dad and I have never
really seen eye to eye.

431
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:11,280
He kicked me out of the house.

432
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:14,840
So, I ran away and never returned.

433
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:18,560
You’re joking, right?

434
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,560
Come on.

435
00:37:20,120 --> 00:37:21,080
Why would I do that?

436
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,080
You can ask anyone on the island.

437
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:24,360
Everyone knows about it.

438
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,640
I was around 15 back then.

439
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:28,800
15?

440
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:30,800
How did you survive?

441
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:32,080
I went to live with my aunt.

442
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:35,480
And did every odd job I could find.

443
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:40,000
I bet you won’t believe
that I've done every job

444
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:41,960
on this island.

445
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,040
Whatever gets me paid, I've done it all.

446
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:47,640
Why won’t you go back home?

447
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:50,840
My dad never takes back what he says.

448
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:54,400
I suppose that’s the only thing
we have in common.

449
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:09,440
Do you think I’m pitiful?

450
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,280
If you do...

451
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,560
then I am.

452
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:17,840
If you don’t...

453
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:20,960
then I’m not.

454
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:24,520
But I want to tell you that...

455
00:38:27,040 --> 00:38:27,960
I never pity myself.

456
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:30,960
What about you?

457
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:32,880
Do you pity me?

458
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:37,160
No.

459
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:40,560
Thank you.

460
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:48,720
What about you?

461
00:38:50,320 --> 00:38:51,440
Why did you become a writer?

462
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:54,920
