00:41:54,440 --> 00:42:01,000
𝘊𝘰𝘯𝘯𝘰𝘳 𝘴𝘢𝘺𝘴 𝘪𝘧 𝘺𝘰𝘶’𝘳𝘦 𝘤𝘶𝘳𝘪𝘰𝘶𝘴
𝘢𝘣𝘰𝘶𝘵 𝘗’ 𝘙𝘢𝘬, 𝘧𝘪𝘯𝘥 𝘪𝘵 𝘰𝘶𝘵 𝘺𝘰𝘶𝘳𝘴𝘦𝘭𝘧.

497
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:29,720
Shall we go diving tomorrow?

498
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:44,680
All set.

499
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:51,800
Why is he coming with us?

500
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:56,680
I need an assistant when go diving.

501
00:42:57,360 --> 00:42:59,400
Someone has to control the boat
while I take guests diving.

502
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:04,080
Why does it have to be him?

503
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:07,160
Ai Palm works for me.

504
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:09,640
He only does part-time
shifts at bars at night.

505
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:12,080
He’s usually always with me
during busy seasons.

506
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:25,280
Or do you want to do
something else with me?

507
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:27,880
That’s why you don’t
want him to tag along.

508
00:43:41,320 --> 00:43:42,360
Don’t bite your lip.

509
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:44,960
The more you do it...

510
00:43:47,600 --> 00:43:48,440
the more I want to kiss you.

511
00:44:00,800 --> 00:44:02,120
On the boat sounds interesting.

512
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,360
But you could get seasick.

513
00:44:22,920 --> 00:44:23,880
Why are you smiling?

514
00:44:24,560 --> 00:44:25,280
Are we not setting off?

515
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:30,760
You’re lucky you’re my bro.

516
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:33,120
Let’s go.

517
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:03,080
Wait here.

518
00:45:03,400 --> 00:45:04,120
Be right back.

519
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:15,280
- Ai Palm.
- Yes?

520
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:16,560
I’m gonna dive for an hour.

521
00:45:17,240 --> 00:45:17,840
Okay.

522
00:45:18,440 --> 00:45:19,280
Then…

523
00:45:20,800 --> 00:45:22,920
I’ll start cooking in about half an hour.

524
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,680
Okay.
What’s there to eat?

525
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:26,920
Shrimp and squid.

526
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:28,960
Can he eat raw food?

527
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:31,120
I guess so.

528
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:31,760
Hey!

529
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:37,440
Ai Palm, give me a hand.

530
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:01,800
Weight belt.

531
00:46:03,680 --> 00:46:04,040
Here.

532
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:14,560
𝘞𝘩𝘺 𝘤𝘢𝘯’𝘵 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘭𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘮𝘦 𝘰𝘳 𝘰𝘶𝘳 𝘴𝘰𝘯?

533
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:17,440
If you want me to stay, then pay me.

534
00:47:17,560 --> 00:47:19,480
I’ve given you everything I have.

535
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:21,440
Are you just going to abandon us?

536
00:47:21,440 --> 00:47:22,520
Abandon your son?

537
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:27,400
Why did he leave me, Rak?

538
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:30,400
Is it because I’m pregnant with his baby?

539
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:32,400
I can’t take it anymore.

540
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:38,120
𝘋𝘰𝘯’𝘵 𝘭𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘢𝘯𝘺𝘰𝘯𝘦…

541
00:47:38,720 --> 00:47:40,160
if you don’t want to end up like me.

542
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:17,440
♪ No matter how much I want to love you ♪

543
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:25,280
♪ My heart is afraid of reopening old wounds ♪

544
00:48:25,320 --> 00:48:27,680
♪ Despite my fears ♪

545
00:48:27,840 --> 00:48:34,240
♪ deep down inside, I still hope ♪

546
00:48:34,480 --> 00:48:39,880
♪ that you won’t reopen my old wounds ♪

547
00:49:37,760 --> 00:49:38,720
Have you calmed down?

548
00:49:46,160 --> 00:49:46,920
I know...

549
00:49:48,560 --> 00:49:49,760
that you’re certified for diving.

550
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:52,280
But you know, right?

551
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:55,320
Amateurs don’t dive alone.

552
00:49:56,160 --> 00:49:56,960
They need buddies.

553
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:00,120
You can’t go down solo.

554
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:04,680
I’m sorry.

555
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:08,800
Drink some.

556
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:29,000
Are you okay?

557
00:50:31,120 --> 00:50:32,720
Why did you panic?

558
00:50:43,400 --> 00:50:44,160
Mahasamut.

559
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:48,640
Why is your name Mahasamut?

560
00:50:49,520 --> 00:50:50,160
Strange.

561
00:50:57,120 --> 00:50:58,280
And why is your name Tongrak?

562
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:00,440
It’s strange too.

563
00:51:02,640 --> 00:51:03,680
I’m asking you first.

564
00:51:08,520 --> 00:51:09,760
It’s so that our names can rhyme, I guess.

565
00:51:11,440 --> 00:51:12,520
Did you fail Thai?

566
00:51:12,960 --> 00:51:14,040
They don’t rhyme at all.

567
00:51:16,560 --> 00:51:17,040
Well…

568
00:51:19,240 --> 00:51:19,920
Tongrak. (Must love)

569
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:23,720
Mahasamut.

570
00:51:29,440 --> 00:51:30,120
Ridiculous.

571
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:32,040
Nonsense.

572
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:36,760
Khun Tongrak - Mahasamut.

573
00:51:41,720 --> 00:51:43,000
You must love me.

574
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:50,840
You’re aware, aren’t you?

575
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,280
Love is just a figment
of our imagination.

576
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:03,080
I’m hungry.

577
00:52:24,960 --> 00:52:25,480
Huh?

578
00:52:26,440 --> 00:52:27,400
Where is it?

579
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:30,720
What are you looking for?

580
00:52:34,240 --> 00:52:35,160
Earlier...

581
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:38,080
I saw a reddish-orange fish.

582
00:52:38,960 --> 00:52:40,200
But now it's gone.

583
00:52:42,800 --> 00:52:43,520
You've seen it.

584
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:46,720
Where?

585
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:50,080
In the Tom Yum soup bowl.

586
00:52:55,400 --> 00:52:56,440
You even said it tasted good.

587
00:52:58,320 --> 00:52:59,520
There’s no need to remind me.

588
00:53:05,840 --> 00:53:09,000
Thank you for being born so tasty.

589
00:53:11,720 --> 00:53:13,640
Will you eat me if I’m tasty?

590
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:14,920
No.

591
00:53:15,840 --> 00:53:16,920
Come on.

592
00:53:17,640 --> 00:53:19,120
Even when I’m willing to sacrifice my life?

593
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:21,040
You still won’t eat me?

594
00:53:25,280 --> 00:53:26,360
That’s you because you have to die.

595
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:29,120
I’d rather not eat you if that’s the case.

596
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:36,960
You say love is a figment of imagination.

597
00:53:37,960 --> 00:53:40,360
Yes, it’s something we make up.

598
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:42,840
I like to imagine things.

599
00:53:43,640 --> 00:53:45,080
You want me to buy love?

600
00:53:45,520 --> 00:53:46,800
Just while you’re on the island

601
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:48,440
take your chances with me.

602
00:53:49,880 --> 00:53:50,760
I want to go to your place.

603
00:53:51,840 --> 00:53:52,360
Take me there.

604
00:53:52,600 --> 00:53:54,200
Here, you forgot this.

605
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:55,200
I’m going home.

606
00:53:55,280 --> 00:53:57,880
Where are you going?
Stay with me.

607
00:53:59,120 --> 00:54:00,160
Will you be my girlfriend?

